==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Canted
<hw>Cant"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From 2d
<er>Cant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having angles; <as>as, a six
<ex>canted</ex> bolt head; a <ex>canted</ex> window</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Canted column</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>a column
polygonal in plan.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inclined at an angle to something else; tipped;
sloping.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Canteen</ent>⟦br⟧
